body:
Holy guacamole it’s one week away!!!!!

It’s unbelievable to think that the last time I saw @taylorswift perform I was just finishing high school and about to start university. Now I’ve just finished my degree at uni and am eagerly awaiting graduation.


My friend and I can’t wait to see you next Friday Taylor, block 119 (can’t remember my seats because my mum hid the tickets to try and get me to focus on my uni exams😂😂). But both Lauren and I (yes me and my bff are both called Lauren) can’t wait to see you

summary: #highesthopesnetwork SELFIE CHALLENGE!  Hi everyone! My name is Brianna, but you can call me Bri! I’m 18 years old and about to...
caption:
#highesthopesnetwork SELFIE CHALLENGE!


Hi everyone! My name is Brianna, but you can call me Bri! I’m 18 years old and about to embark on one of the biggest adventures in life- COLLEGE! 

I have been a fan of Taylor ever since I was seven years old, bopping around to breakup songs I didn’t know anything about yet. I did and loved ALL things Taylor, from begging my mom for T-shirts, to buying the Taylor Swift dolls, to having her face on my birthday cakes, to even entering a local contest to win tickets to her show, where I reenacted her 2008 ACM performance; minus the water, plus ALL the sass (which i can post if you guys want a good laugh). I didn’t win, but my love for Taylor continued to thrive. 

Now that I’m older, I still obsess over Taylor just like I did as a tiny little bean. I make my own pins, I create reputaion inspired makeup, but most of all, I feel and live through Taylor’s music. Taylor Alison Swift has helped me through all the toughest moments in my life, including a mentally abusive relationship. I’ve related to Taylor through Dear John, All Too Well, and so many more songs. Because of her, I’ve had someone to carry me through my heartbreaks and show me the light at the end of the tunnel. Now, with her help, I’m doing better than I EVER was :)

This fall I’ll be attending college as a Musical Theatre major, and I owe my thanks to Taylor not only for the courage she gave me to audition, but the empowerment she gave me as a woman and a victim of abuse to stand up for myself AND my music, and to never stop pursuing my dreams. 

Thank you Taylor for all the memories and mentorship!! I LOVE YOU!!! :)

caption:
Backgrid Exclusive! Taylor Swift and Joe Alwyn have a pub lunch in London! 🍻

Taylor Swift and British boyfriend Joe Alwyn make a swift exit out of the side door of a traditional English pub in North London after a lunch date. The couple looked happy and relaxed as they were escorted to their waiting blacked out Volvo after spending 45mins together. It is reported the couple enjoyed traditional fish and chips along with 2 pints of London Pride beer… maybe Joe was showing Taylor his English roots!
